<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-9555] HA functionality that uses ZooKeeper may experience inadvertent TCP RST and miss session expiration event due to bug in client connection management</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9555</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1702&quot; title=&quot;ZooKeeper client may write operation packets before receiving successful response to connection request, can cause TCP RST&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-1702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-1702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tracks a client connection management bug.  The bug can cause an unexpected TCP RST that ultimately prevents delivery of a session expiration event.  The symptoms of the bug seem to show up more frequently on Windows than on other platforms (though it&apos;s not really a Windows-specific bug).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12646863">HADOOP-9555</key>
            <summary>HA functionality that uses ZooKeeper may experience inadvertent TCP RST and miss session expiration event due to bug in client connection management</summary>
