                            <comment id="13653152" author="cnauroth" created="Thu, 9 May 2013 20:31:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The scope of this issue is to upgrade Hadoop Common&apos;s ZooKeeper version after resolution of that bug and get the failing tests to run and pass consistently on Windows.  This bug causes sporadic failures in the following tests on Windows: &lt;tt&gt;TestActiveStandbyElectorRealZK&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;TestFailoverController&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;TestZKFailoverController&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;TestZKFailoverControllerStress&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016168" author="raviprak" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 03:02:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this specific to Windows? &lt;tt&gt;TestZKFailoverControllerStress&lt;/tt&gt; seems to fail intermittently for me too&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025776" author="cnauroth" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 21:30:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The underlying ZooKeeper bug is not really a Windows-specific problem.  I was only able to repro on Windows, but it&apos;s theoretically possible on any platform.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see that ZooKeeper 3.4.6 has been released, which included the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1702&quot; title=&quot;ZooKeeper client may write operation packets before receiving successful response to connection request, can cause TCP RST&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-1702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-1702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix.  That means we can proceed with upgrading the dependency here in Hadoop.  I&apos;ll take a look at that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://zookeeper.apache.org/doc/r3.4.6/releasenotes.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://zookeeper.apache.org/doc/r3.4.6/releasenotes.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025927" author="cnauroth" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 23:26:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch upgrading to ZooKeeper 3.4.6.  I ran a subset of tests relevant to our ZK integration on both Mac and Windows, and they passed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14025951" author="hadoopqa" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 23:58:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt;-1 overall&lt;/font&gt;.  Here are the results of testing the latest attachment &lt;br/&gt;
